cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with fixpoint logics and their complexity analysis. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses extensions of probabilistic and graded mu-calculi, which are relevant to AI applications. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper presents a new caching algorithm for practical use. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper deals with the satisfiability problem for a logic and its extensions. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper provides upper bounds on the complexity of satisfiability checking.
